author: @ritikkohad5045
text: For the people who are getting confused between cosine similarity and cosine distance. In cosine similarity if the value is towards 1 then it would be considered as very similar. If the value is towards 0 then there is no or less similarity between the two points or vectors. In the video at 26:50 Krish sir is  talking about cosine distance not cosine similarity. So in cosine distance if the value is more towards 0 then there is a similarity between the points or vectors and vice versa.
